# [A] Risotto (instapot)

## Ingredients

- White Wine | ¾ cup | 
- Mushrooms | 3 cups | Sliced
- Arborio Rice | 1 ½ cups | 
- Chicken Stock | 9/10th quart | 
- Parmesan Cheese | ½ cup | Grated
- Onion | 1 cup chopped | 
- Unsalted Butter | ¼ cup | 
- Rosemary Or Thyme | 1 sprig or 1/4 tsp | 
- Olive Oil | ¼ cup | 

> Instructions

Set instapot to sauté, put 9/10 of quart of chicken stock on a hob

Add butter and olive oil; stir until butter melts, about 2 minutes.

Add onions, cook, season

Add garlic, cook

Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, about 3 minutes.

Add rosemary sprig (or thyme); cook for 1 minute.

Stir rice into the pot until each grain is coated with butter-olive oil mixture, about 2 minutes.

Pour in wine; simmer for 3 minutes.

Pour in chicken stock, stirring to scrape the sides of the pot. Simmer for 1 minute.

Pressure cook 6 minutes

Boil peas

Toast pine nuts

Force release pressure

Discard rosemary sprig

Add peas

Stir risotto until creamy, about 1 minute.

Season with salt and pepper. Stir in Parmesan cheese until melted and combined.
